EN: Cranes symbolize longevity and good fortune in Chinese culture.
ZH: 仙鹤是世界上最大的鸟类之一。
EN: Cranes are one of the largest birds in the world.
ZH: 仙鹤通常生活在湿地和沼泽地区。
EN: Cranes typically inhabit wetlands and marshy areas.
ZH: 仙鹤具有优雅的飞行姿态。
EN: Cranes have graceful flying postures.
ZH: 我希望有一天能亲眼看到野生的仙鹤。
EN: I hope to see wild cranes with my own eyes one day.
ZH: 仙鹤的翅膀非常宽大，可以展开飞翔。
EN: Cranes have broad wings that can extend for flight.
ZH: 仙鹤的响亮叫声能在远处听到。
EN: The loud calls of a crane can be heard from afar.
ZH: 仙鹤通常是一夫一妻制的。
EN: Cranes are usually monogamous birds.
ZH: 仙鹤会通过跳舞来表达自己的情感。
EN: Cranes express their emotions through dancing.
ZH: 仙鹤的叫声有一种神秘的美感。
EN: The call of a crane has a mysterious beauty.
ZH: 仙鹤的嘴部非常长且尖锐。
EN: Cranes have long and sharp beaks.
ZH: 许多人将仙鹤视为神圣的生物。
EN: Many people consider cranes as sacred creatures.
ZH: 仙鹤是一种濒危的物种。
EN: Cranes are an endangered species.
ZH: 仙鹤被列为野生动物保护的重点对象。
EN: Cranes are listed as a priority species for wildlife conservation.
